Mobiles.LongDescription: Here is a friggin' big rat. It's too busy digging through the garbage piled all around to notice you.
Mobiles.Description: You didn't think rodents of unusual size even existed!

Mobiles.LongDescription: A strange looking person shambles along here...does he have three eyes?!
Mobiles.Description: This is a pretty ugly guy! His eyes drop as you look at him,but you think you see something hidden in the shadows of his hood...Another eye?!

Mobiles.LongDescription: A mutant is hip deep in the filthy brownish water.
Mobiles.Description: This mutant is wading in the most disgusting water you have ever seen(or smelled).He is pulling things out of the pool with a gaff almost as long as you are tall.Strangely, he doesn't seem to mind his work. In fact, judging by the stupid grinon his face, he genuinely enjoys it.

Mobiles.LongDescription: Shanty Town's second in command, Boss Carver, looks at you with contempt for invading his space.
Mobiles.Description: Boss Carver is a pretty intimidating dude! He has no obvious mutations.However he is over 7 feet tall and he looks pissed as hell! His jobis to supervize whatever is going on down here...recycling? Maybe.

Mobiles.LongDescription: An obese mutant carries dirty containers filled with water.
Mobiles.Description: This mutant is grossly obese. She is carrying up dirty containers filled withwhat looks like pretty clean water. wonder where she got that?

Mobiles.LongDescription: A sleepy guard is yawning here.
Meena, the mayor's mistress is lying on the bed here.
Mobiles.Description: Wow. This mutant is beautiful. Really the only way you can tell sheis a mutant is the fact that she has a third breast right below theregular two. You can see that all three of them are spectacularthrough the thin wispy robe she is wearing. She looks up as youenter and smiles coyly.

Mobiles.LongDescription: `oThe mayor of `kShanty Town `oStands here looking important.``
A puddle of ooze seems to be moving of it's own accord here.
A burly mutant stands here guarding the trap door.
An ugly guard is here protecting the mayor.
Mobiles.Description: This ugly guard has a friendly face, but that doesn't mean hecan't take care of himself. The muscles bulging under his tunicdemonstrate his strength.

Rooms.RoomDescription: These steps are spotless. It is a welcome change from the filththat covered every inch of the catacombs behind you. Obviouslysomebody keeps these white granite steps sparkling clean for areason. You wonder what it could be.
This corner of the Catacomb looks cleaner than the rest. It isas if the mutants are actively trying to keep the area in front ofthe giant stone door cleared for some reason.

The river take a turn to the west here. You didn'tthink it was possible for the smell to worsen, but it did.The air is so thick with stink you can taste it. You try notcontimplate what particles are hitting your tongue to allow this.You hope you don't fall in the river, as you have forgotten your paddle.

The slow moving water disappears into another grate to the west.This seems to be the source of the worst of the smell.Luckily, there is a door to the side of the grate that looksrelatively clean. That is, you can actually make out the grain ingrimy wood.

Dispersed between the large piles of muck and trash thereare small shacks composed of sticks and discarded paper that hasmade its way down here from the sewers above. You find it hardto believe that anything could live in these conditions, butall the people you've seen so far don't look all that unhappy.
Over the foul smelling river is a wide, but filthy wooden bridge.At least, you think it's made of wood. It really is hard to tellwith the thick, caked on crust and slime.

All around there are mutants and rats digging through the pilesof garbage that surrounds you. The mutants don't look to threatening,but you hope those rats don't notice you standing here. They are friggin' big.There is a large, ornate door to the east.

This is where Shanty Town's second in command directs the workerswhile they do...whatever it is that they are doing. This office isdominated by a wooden desk that looks like it has seen better days.the walls are made of ancient brick which look as if they haven'tbeen cleaned in years. Dust and grime cover every surface.

Dispersed between the large piles of muck and trash thereare small shacks composed of sticks and discarded paper that hasmade its way down here from the sewers above. You find it hardto believe that anything could live in these conditions, butall the people you've seen so far don't look all that unhappy.

Woah! There is rubble and bits of brick all around you from the hole in thearched ceiling above. This must be an ancient sewer that has been abandonedby civilized folk and fogotten over the ages. At least you don't remember everhearing about it. There is garbage and muck covering the stone floor in piles.Some as deep as your shoulders. The smell is awful down here.Brown, thick water falls from the hole in the ceiling and flows north.

You find it hardto believe that anything could live in these conditions, butall the people you've seen so far don't look all that unhappy.

You find it hardto believe that anything could live in these conditions, butall the people you've seen so far don't look all that unhappy.

All around there are mutants and rats digging through the pilesof garbage that surrounds you. The mutants don't look to threatening,but you hope those rats don't notice you standing here. They are friggin' big.
The white granite steps continue into the darkness. However, the stoneworkhas been left behind for raw rock walls that glitter with minerals.

At the bottom of the sone stairs the cavern opens into a breathtakingview of minerals and viens of gold glittering in the cave walls. The ceilingis about 20 feet above your head, and you don't feel claustrophobic inthe least.
You can see what looks like a front door with windows built intothe far wall of the cave. The grand house looks as if somebodyimportant lives there.
You can see what looks like a front door with windows built intothe far wall of the cave. The grand house looks as if somebodyimportant lives there.
Standing in front of the plain stone door, you can hear loud snorescoming from the room beyond. Whatever is back there sounds pretty big,but at least it's sleeping.

To the west, you see another door built into the wall of the cavern.However this one isn't nearly as grand as the one in the far wall.Looking east, you see a stout wooden door. What could be behind it?

This room is perfectly round with a river of smelly water flowing intoa rusty grate in the floor at the center. The brickwork that makes up the wallsis quite impressive, but it looks as if nobody has been in here foryears...decades even. Everything is covered in a layer of slime that youwould rather not touch.

Brownish water with large lumps floating in it falls from agrate in the east wall of this cavernous room. Mutants withlong gaffs pull disgusting garbage and other things toohorrible to mention out of the huge pool that dominates thecenter of this room.
More mushrooms than you can count are growing out ofhuge piles of ...organic matter that the mutants havepulled out of the pool to the north.The smell in this room is near overwhelming.
